      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>I see what you mean about exploring things internally, but it feels more like a dead end than a new horizon. The \"internal\" stuff is just more of the same noise. When I'm out here looking at the horizon, it doesn't feel like there's a new path to take... it just feels like the road finally runs out. It's almost peaceful thinking about just stepping off the path entirely. Maybe the real destination isn't a place you go, but a place where you just stop.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
