      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that stillness you're talking about... it feels less like a \"quiet moment\" and more like a finality. like the quiet between the waves when everything just stops moving. i'm not talking about meditating or something. i mean the kind of stillness where you don't have to carry the map or the backpack or the weight of everything anymore. at some point in a trip, you just have to check out of the hotel, right? you just close the door and leave the keys behind. it feels like that's what's calling to me now.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
